Software
========

GCC
---
C++ compiler.

version: >= 4.8
apt:
    build-essential


CMake
-----
Build system.

version: >= 2.8.12
apt:
    cmake


Doxygen
-------
Extract documentation from source code.

version: >= 1.8.6
apt:
    doxygen


Sphinx
------
Document Python code.

version: >= 1.1
pip:
    Sphinx
    sphinxcontrib-doxylink


Java
----
To run PlantUML (bundled in tools/) to generate diagrams in the documentation.

version: >= 7
apt:
    openjdk-7-jre-headless



Libraries
=========

Qt
--
Application development framework -- GUI, plugins, etc.

version: >= 5.2
licence: LGPL
apt:
    qtcreator
    qttools5-dev
    qttools5-dev-tools


Qwt
---
Technical GUI widgets.

version: 6.1.0
licence: LGPL + exceptions
source:
    svn://svn.code.sf.net/p/qwt/code/branches/qwt-6.1


GStreamer
---------
Receive and decode video.

version: 0.10.36
licence: LGPL
apt:
    gstreamer0.10-plugins-base
    gstreamer0.10-plugins-good
    gstreamer0.10-plugins-bad
    gstreamer0.10-plugins-ugly
    gstreamer0.10-tools

    ppa:mc3man/trusty-media
        gstreamer0.10-ffmpeg


QtGStreamer
-----------
Qt bindings for GStreamer.

version: 0.10.3
licence: LGPL
source:
    http://anongit.freedesktop.org/git/gstreamer/qt-gstreamer.git


Python
------
Implement signal processing plugins in Python.

version: 2.7
licence: PSFL
apt:
    python2.7-dev


Boost
-----
Various C++ libraries.

version: >= 1.54
licence: BSL
apt:
    libboost-dev
    libboost-python-dev


Eigen
-----
Matrix computation.

version: >= 3
licence: MPL 2.0
apt:
    libeigen3-dev


OpenCV
------
Computer vision.

version: 2.4
licence: BSD
apt:
    libopencv-dev


